1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,461
Good thing your island
is peaceful now, Sitti.

2
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:05,964
I hope your island
remains peaceful from now on.

3
00:00:06,047 --> 00:00:08,341
[Jamilah] <i>And everything will be alright.</i>

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:10,844
<i>After all the suffering comes relief.</i>

5
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,387
Reyes? Why are you still here?

6
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:13,763
Didn't Doc invite us for dinner?

7
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,391
- She invited you?
- [Jalil] Yeah. Let's go together.

8
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,727
- Are you okay, Ma?
- I'm just so happy

9
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:23,398
because it's like… it's been so long
since we had a meal together. [sniffles]

10
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:24,774
Marcus's brother went missing.

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:27,902
[Jalil] <i>I'm adopted.</i>
<i>What if I'm actually Gabriel?</i>

12
00:00:27,986 --> 00:00:29,904
[Lara] <i>Before, our problem</i>
<i>was only Agent Reyes,</i>

13
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:33,366
<i>but now, even Major Espina</i>
<i>could be a big problem.</i>

14
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:35,660
[in English] And-- And they're working
with each other, I'm sure of it.

15
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,245
Did you know about that?!

16
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:38,788
[Manuel] <i>Answer me!</i>

17
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,707
- Yes.
- [Manuel] <i>Look at what's happening.</i>

18
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:41,583
Huh?

19
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:46,421
[Manuel] <i>Datu Rahman</i>
<i>is in Mustapha's hands!</i>

20
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:52,218
Just imagine the things
he'll hear from Datu Rahman!

21
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:54,262
[Ahmad] <i>About our secret.</i>

22
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:56,890
Don't blame yourself with what happened

23
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:57,807
to our brothers and sisters.

24
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:01,519
It's better if you tell this
to your children.

25
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,856
[Ahmad] <i>Tell them the truth.</i>
<i>Be honest with them.</i>

26
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:08,651
<i>Jalil is putting his life on the line</i>

27
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,944
<i>just to clear your name.</i>

28
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:11,029
[Marcus] <i>This wasn't a suicide.</i>

29
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:13,198
<i>They did the same thing</i>
<i>to Colonel Del Mundo.</i>

30
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:14,574
[Jalil] <i>They always get ahead of us.</i>

31
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,534
<i>They're used to silencing people.</i>

32
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:27,712
[mysterious theme music playing]

33
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:39,808
[in English] Goddammit, Reyes.

34
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:42,811
[in English] To my office, now!

35
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:44,813
[in English] Follow me!

36
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:50,735
[tense music playing]

37
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,837
[in English] Goddammit, Reyes.

38
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,089
I thought you were being careful?!

39
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,174
How are we gonna cover this up now?!

40
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:14,134
[inhales sharply]

41
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:15,927
Sir, I was careful!

42
00:02:16,636 --> 00:02:17,846
Sir, it's already been a long time

43
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:19,639
since I took Datu Rahman in.

44
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:22,016
They only secured that video recently.

45
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,601
If they've had it for a long time,

46
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:24,561
they would've spread it long ago.

47
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:29,274
Whoever uploaded that video
has various informants.

48
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:31,401
They're the ones who are sabotaging us.

49
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:33,403
‪[scoffs]

50
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:35,780
Because of that damn video,

51
00:02:36,364 --> 00:02:39,075
our mission is not the only thing
in danger,

52
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:42,787
but even your life and your position!

53
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:45,623
We can't lose you right now, Reyes!

54
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:48,167
They can use a lot of things against you.

55
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:51,296
They can even lay you off, you know?!

56
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,465
I'm not afraid anymore, sir.

57
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:58,261
Even if they fire me,

58
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,348
I'll still finish what we started.

59
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:06,978
[music intensifies]

60
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,194
Without a doubt,
a syndicate is behind this.

61
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,406
They want to taint Marcus's name.

62
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:19,908
I have to help him.

63
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,910
What're you going to do?

64
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:24,162
Hmm?

65
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:29,709
Are you going to confess
that you're in cahoots

66
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:31,336
with him in taking Datu Rahman?

67
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:33,671
Usman, NLEA was only able
to bring in results now,

68
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,590
and that is because of Marcus.

69
00:03:35,673 --> 00:03:37,592
The reason they leaked that video

70
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:39,510
is because Marcus
is a huge threat to them.

71
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:43,306
And they want to silence him.

72
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:44,599
That's exactly why!

73
00:03:44,682 --> 00:03:45,683
We need to take action.

74
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:47,602
We can't just sit here and do nothing.

75
00:03:47,685 --> 00:03:49,103
This agency needs Marcus!

76
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:51,064
I know that! But we have to be
even more cautious.

77
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:53,816
Don't get yourself in trouble.

78
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,444
You're one of the remaining officers
who's not corrupt.

79
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:58,404
The agency needs you too.

80
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:00,114
Usman,

81
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,866
the people we are going against,

82
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:03,785
they're powerful.

83
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:08,248
You won't be able to help Marcus
if you're in danger too.

84
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:11,376
[tense music playing]

85
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:14,629
‪[music intensifies]

86
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:28,142
[Andre sighs]

87
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:29,644
What will happen now?

88
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,313
[Liam] Guys,

89
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:33,898
Sir Marcus's video is everywhere.

90
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:35,900
There's a lot of negative reactions.

91
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:39,904
Sir Marcus and Director Azuelo
are talking right now.

92
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,739
The situation is really dire.

93
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:44,492
Surely they're already thinking
of a solution, right?

94
00:04:44,575 --> 00:04:45,535
[sighs]

95
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:46,911
But what do you think, guys?

96
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:48,162
Do you think the video is legit?

97
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:50,581
It could be AI-generated, plus…

98
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,667
why would Sir Marcus hide Datu Rahman?

99
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,168
He's probably got a reason.

100
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:56,379
Sir Marcus?

101
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:57,422
[scoffs]

102
00:04:57,505 --> 00:04:59,716
He wouldn't do such a thing
without a good reason.

103
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,384
That's right.

104
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:03,553
That's why we shouldn't doubt him.

105
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,179
You sure about that?

106
00:05:06,347 --> 00:05:07,181
[Felix scoffs]

107
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:09,642
We went through a lot

108
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,270
just to find Datu Rahman.

109
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:14,772
[grim music playing]

110
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:16,983
A lot of our colleagues died that night.

111
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,361
But he didn't tell us

112
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,364
that he already captured Datu Rahman.

113
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:25,533
[Liam] I'm sorry, sir, but…

114
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:28,328
it's obvious that someone just wants
to dishonor Sir Marcus's name.

115
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:29,954
We shouldn't let it get to us.

116
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,249
You weren't there that night.

117
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:37,128
So, I understand why
you're not mad at Sir Marcus.

118
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,215
But aren't we a team?

119
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:43,509
Aren't we allies?

120
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:45,762
And allies

121
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,598
don't keep secrets from each other.

122
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:50,058
[Andre] Sir.

123
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:53,102
I think it's better if we wait
for Sir Marcus's explanation.

124
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,521
[snickers]

125
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:58,816
Yeah, he's gonna give
an explanation. Probably.

126
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,530
But of course, I can't help
but feel frustrated.

127
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:06,532
I mean…

128
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:10,078
he made us look like…

129
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,037
[clicks tongue]

130
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,121
…fools.

131
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:16,000
We understand where
you're coming from, sir.

132
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,378
But I hope we don't
let ourselves get led on

133
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,839
by those who are doing this to Sir Marcus.

134
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:24,342
This is surely what they want to happen.

135
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,930
Sir Marcus is doing everything
for the truth, sir.

136
00:06:29,013 --> 00:06:30,473
Naturally,

137
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:33,142
they'd do everything to destroy him too.

138
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:36,813
And he trusts us TFA members
to remain by his side,

139
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:38,898
believing in him.

140
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:42,902
So, you're like dogs then.

141
00:06:42,985 --> 00:06:44,529
What loyalty.

142
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:48,157
You could even howl.

143
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:53,496
[howling]

144
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:57,250
[laughing, howling]

145
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:02,755
[music intensifies]

146
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,423
- Sir.
- [pats]

147
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:05,591
- Sir.
- [pats]

148
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:13,433
[Mia] <i>We were made to believe</i>

149
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:15,351
<i>that Datu Rahman has gone missing.</i>

150
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:19,188
<i>Turns out, Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>is merely hiding him!</i>

151
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,816
<i>Isn't that kidnapping?!</i>

152
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,734
<i>He should be charged with a crime!</i>

153
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:28,448
[morose music playing]

154
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,199
My son…

155
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,284
[Jamilah] Doc.

156
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:32,952
[Teresa] Jamilah.

157
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:36,080
We don't know if what
she's saying is true, right?

158
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,541
It might be AI-generated.

159
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:41,085
Why would my son do this to your father?

160
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:43,337
[exhales shakily]

161
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:44,755
Doc…

162
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,675
The video is authentic.

163
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:49,677
Huh?

164
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,971
Marcus hid my father.

165
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:56,392
Doc, I know about it.

166
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:58,644
My father talked to me about it

167
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:01,272
before he surrendered himself
to Ahmad Mustapha.

168
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:03,357
Huh… Uh…

169
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:06,527
But I know

170
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:09,572
that Marcus did it to protect my father.

171
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:14,076
And I also know that your son
is not a bad person.

172
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:17,413
[somber music playing]

173
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,957
[breathes deeply]

174
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:27,673
Whoever is behind this
aims to silence you.

175
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:31,469
I'll find out who they are,

176
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:33,596
so I could help you out a bit.

177
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,431
[pensive music playing]

178
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:41,437
That would be great, Espina. Thank you.

179
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:43,606
Marcus.

180
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:45,775
What's this?

181
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:48,444
[in English] Is it true?
You had Datu Rahman this whole time?

182
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,156
[sighs heavily]

183
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,283
[grim music playing]

184
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,328
[clears throat]

185
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:02,208
I wish you won't run my ears off, Lara.

186
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,127
I won't run your ears off, Marcus.

187
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,506
[in English] Don't you get it?
We're supposed to be a team.

188
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:11,050
You're putting yourself in danger.

189
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,802
And I don't know how to help you

190
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,220
because you're not asking for my help.

191
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:20,518
Because I don't trust anyone here, Lara.

192
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:22,979
[in English] Even me?!

193
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,981
[grim music continues]

194
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:28,317
[in English] Yes, including you.

195
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,610
[Lara scoffs]

196
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,744
We've been friends
for a long time, Marcus.

197
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:41,664
[in English] And I've had your back
for so many years.

198
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:52,925
[phone buzzing]

199
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:55,469
Sir.

200
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:57,305
[Azuelo] <i>Agent Reyes.</i>

201
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,140
<i>The higher ups are summoning you.</i>

202
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:01,892
[in English] Yes, sir.

203
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:05,146
[suspenseful music playing]

204
00:10:19,827 --> 00:10:21,412
Agent Reyes.

205
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:25,333
Is what this video shows true?

206
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,460
[tense music playing]

207
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,797
[in English] Yes, sir.

208
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,301
- You mean to tell me…
- [clacks]

209
00:10:36,093 --> 00:10:39,847
while your teammates
were looking for Datu Rahman,

210
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:44,727
you were hiding him yourself?

211
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:48,939
Sir, Datu Rahman was kidnapped
and locked up in the Zylverix building.

212
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:53,569
I helped him break out to protect him.

213
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:56,405
Because I know

214
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,659
that even if he's under our custody,

215
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:01,911
his life could still be in danger.

216
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:06,415
Because there are traitors within NLEA.

217
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:08,250
- [bangs on table]
- [in English] Stop saying that!

218
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,127
But it's the truth, sir.

219
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,380
[in English] Those allegations

220
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:15,257
are still under investigation.

221
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,429
If you don't have a strong evidence,

222
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:25,017
don't you dare dishonor
the name of this agency!

223
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:27,019
Especially in front of me!

224
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,981
You have so many violations, Reyes,

225
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:33,109
illegal detention,

226
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,610
kidnapping,

227
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:38,280
and yet you have the nerve
to speak about other officers

228
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:41,033
when you're the one who's out of control!

229
00:11:41,617 --> 00:11:43,619
You are the traitor here!

230
00:11:43,702 --> 00:11:45,830
[music intensifies]

231
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:54,964
Agent Reyes.

232
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:58,509
[in English] You are hereby placed…

233
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:04,807
under preventive suspension.

234
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,600
[music turns somber]

235
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:07,935
Effective…

236
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:10,896
immediately!

237
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:13,190
[dramatic sting]

238
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:01,155
[in English] You know what to do.

239
00:13:04,742 --> 00:13:06,035
[in English] Yes, Dad.

240
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,245
[morose music playing]

241
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,999
[pen thuds]

242
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:16,754
[breathing heavily]

243
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:19,298
You took Datu Rahman from me.

244
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:26,430
Because of you, Marcus,
I broke Dad's trust.

245
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,809
I failed to avenge my parents.

246
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,605
[in English] You deserve this, Marcus.

247
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:35,898
[in English] You deserve this.

248
00:13:38,984 --> 00:13:40,528
[objects thud]

249
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:43,155
[Lara grunts angrily]

250
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:47,409
[panting]

251
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:49,620
[morose music playing]

252
00:13:59,213 --> 00:14:01,423
[somber music playing]

253
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:08,389
Sir.

254
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,308
Major Espina.

255
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:14,728
General.

256
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:19,275
How's your investigation
into my daughter going?

257
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,778
Have you… found anything?

258
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,989
[in English] Hmm? Nothing?

259
00:14:25,614 --> 00:14:26,740
[scoffs]

260
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:28,033
[in English] I see.

261
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,034
[tongue clicks]

262
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,954
I thought you were good,

263
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:36,709
that's why the Muslim affairs
sent you here.

264
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:42,047
Then why did you fail
to apprehend Marcus Reyes?

265
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:48,345
All this time, he was the one
who hid Datu Rahman.

266
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:52,182
Sir, the investigation is still ongoing.

267
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:55,519
And Reyes isn't the only suspect
in Datu Rahman's abduction.

268
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:57,938
[scoffs, in English] Really?

269
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:01,066
That contradicts what I saw in the video.

270
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:04,486
Oh, sir. One video

271
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,281
from an anonymous account
is not enough proof.

272
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:11,493
[snickers]

273
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:17,374
You seem to really trust Reyes, huh?

274
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,001
- Why, Espina?
- [Jalil] General.

275
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:20,169
Let me ask you the same thing, sir.

276
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:25,633
Why do you seem so sure
that Reyes was the culprit?

277
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:29,053
You made your case
just because of one video,

278
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:30,596
sir?

279
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,348
[music intensifies]

280
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:37,019
[Jalil] General.

281
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:43,108
[music intensifies]

282
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,367
[pensive music playing]

283
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,077
What?

284
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:55,162
You're on preventive suspension?

285
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:58,916
[Liam] But, sir…

286
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,002
just temporarily, right?

287
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:05,631
Sir, what will happen to our operation
while you're away?

288
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:06,715
She's right, sir.

289
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:11,762
[Marcus] I'm sorry.

290
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:15,808
Because of what happened,
Task Force Alpha might get reprimanded.

291
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,101
"I'm sorry," that's it?

292
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:22,773
We're purging our ranks!
TFA, NLEA, and even SID.

293
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:25,651
And you, our supposed leader,

294
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:27,569
this is on you.

295
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,697
[tense music playing]

296
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:33,575
- [Felix] Right?
- I did it to protect Datu Rahman.

297
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,285
Because he is telling the truth.

298
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:43,335
The people responsible
for the massacre on the island

299
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:45,087
were among our ranks.

300
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:51,135
We don't know who they are as of now,

301
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,220
but they're here.

302
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:56,515
Right here, in this very agency.

303
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:03,939
Reyes is telling the truth.

304
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:04,857
‪[music intensifies]

305
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:12,156
Datu Rahman told me everything.

306
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:14,408
He surrendered himself to me.

307
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:18,037
Reyes did that to protect him.

308
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:23,834
He kept him away from the chaos.

309
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,757
What will happen now, sir?

310
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:33,969
I don't know if…

311
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:38,223
I'm going to lose my job.

312
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,603
But no matter what happens,

313
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,814
I trust that you'll do everything

314
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:50,235
to find the traitor within our agency.

315
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:51,779
‪[dramatic tense music playing]

316
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:53,614
They need to be held accountable

317
00:17:53,697 --> 00:17:57,367
for all the turmoil
and violence they've caused.

318
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:03,999
Reyes.

319
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:05,626
The fight is not over.

320
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:09,171
I'm sure they'll give you your job back.

321
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,174
Because Task Force Alpha needs you.

322
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:19,223
While I'm suspended,

323
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:24,978
Major Allan Espina
will be your team leader.

324
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,438
‪[dramatic music playing]

325
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:31,735
[Lara] Hold on.

326
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:33,862
Aren't you even going to consult me?

327
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:36,031
[music turns pensive]

328
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,407
You're suspended, right?

329
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:41,078
You can't just assign someone for this.

330
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:44,039
And you're the one who kept reiterating

331
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,958
that he's not even a part of TFA.

332
00:18:47,584 --> 00:18:50,379
He has been with us
on some of our missions.

333
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:54,466
And if you're looking
for someone with expertise,

334
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,719
Major Espina is also experienced
in leading a team.

335
00:18:58,428 --> 00:18:59,930
[Lara exhales]

336
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:02,808
[in English] With all due respect, ma'am.

337
00:19:02,891 --> 00:19:05,435
I have no problem taking command
from Major Espina.

338
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:07,146
I'm not talking to you.

339
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:09,565
[Liam] Me too, ma'am.

340
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:11,567
No problem with me.

341
00:19:16,446 --> 00:19:17,739
Me too, ma'am.

342
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:20,951
Me too.

343
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:25,831
Hmm?

344
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:38,635
[door opens, shuts]

345
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:40,053
Sure.

346
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,097
Me too.

347
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,223
Whatever pleases you.

348
00:19:43,932 --> 00:19:45,225
I'll leave it to you.

349
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,106
[Felix sniffs]

350
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,279
Don't worry, Reyes.

351
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:01,533
I'll take care of Task Force Alpha.

352
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:03,243
I promise.

353
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,748
We'll wait for you, brother.

354
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:09,416
[sentimental music playing]

355
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:34,524
- [in English] Not now, Felix!
- [tense music playing]

356
00:20:35,317 --> 00:20:36,693
Madam.

357
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:37,736
Calm down.

358
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:40,405
How will I calm down?! [scoffs]

359
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,157
Marcus doesn't trust me!

360
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:43,700
[in English] He's even
being vocal about it.

361
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:46,370
He didn't tell me he got Datu Rahman.

362
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:48,538
How can I control him

363
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:50,332
if he doesn't trust me?!

364
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:51,667
[sighs]

365
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,752
Why are you so angry?

366
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:54,795
Marcus was right.

367
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:57,714
- Huh?
- You should not be trusted.

368
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:00,676
Lara.

369
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,470
Calm down.

370
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:09,434
You're always isolating yourself
from the group.

371
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,562
Marcus is suspended.

372
00:21:12,646 --> 00:21:15,440
He's about to lose his job.

373
00:21:15,524 --> 00:21:18,277
Soon enough, you won't need his trust.

374
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:20,445
Lara,

375
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:24,074
you've already won.

376
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,410
That's why

377
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:29,579
you should mingle with Task Force Alpha.

378
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:31,498
Don't isolate.

379
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:34,126
You need to manipulate them,

380
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:36,044
not Marcus.

381
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:37,671
[dramatic sting]

382
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,134
‪[dramatic sting]

383
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:54,354
‪[music intensifies]

384
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:04,948
There can be no mishaps
at this investment summit.

385
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,117
[in English] A lot depends on this.

386
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,869
Can I count on you?

387
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:10,412
[in English] Of course, sir.

388
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:13,332
NLEA has your back.

389
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:14,791
[in English] Good.

390
00:22:15,751 --> 00:22:16,585
Sir.

391
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:19,421
[pensive music playing]

392
00:22:34,102 --> 00:22:35,520
[in English] Good evening, General.

393
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:38,065
Hmm.

394
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:38,982
‪[snickers]

395
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:43,653
[in English] Agent Marcus Reyes,

396
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:47,616
the Golden Boy of SID.

397
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:50,035
[sighs]

398
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:54,414
I never thought that you

399
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:56,958
would embarrass this agency.

400
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:00,170
[sighs] How disappointing.

401
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:03,381
Sir, I did what was right.

402
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:08,136
I kept everything silent
because I don't trust anyone here, sir.

403
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,764
I have been leading here for decades.

404
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:14,810
All the officers and staff know me.

405
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:16,937
I am respected.

406
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:22,901
[in English] These are all hardworking
and loyal individuals.

407
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:28,490
[scoffs] And you're saying
that they can't be trusted?!

408
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:31,326
‪[music intensifies]

409
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:33,495
Sir, that's not what I meant.

410
00:23:33,578 --> 00:23:34,788
[annoyed sigh]

411
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:58,687
[dramatic tense music playing]

412
00:24:04,651 --> 00:24:07,571
The generals are handling
the verdict tomorrow, Ma.

413
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:11,032
[Marcus] <i>I don't know</i>
<i>how I'd feel if I get laid off.</i>

414
00:24:11,116 --> 00:24:14,411
<i>I feel like Gabriel will be disappointed.</i>

415
00:24:14,494 --> 00:24:16,496
I hope Allah guides you.

416
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:18,498
[Lara] How did you get along
with Agent Reyes?

417
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:20,709
Did he trust you with Task Force Alpha?

418
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:24,588
I'm not the enemy,
but there are enemies around.

419
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:28,425
[Manuel] We will take
the resources of the police.

420
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:33,555
Which one of you is the brains
behind all of this?

421
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:37,726
[Ahmad] <i>There is one hand running you all.</i>

422
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:41,229
[Jalil] <i>Lara.</i>

423
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:43,815
<i>You'll be the key</i>

424
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:46,193
<i>to answering all my questions.</i>

425
00:24:46,276 --> 00:24:48,737
[Ethan] <i>The company's fleet schedule</i>

426
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,530
<i>is still ongoing.</i>

427
00:24:50,614 --> 00:24:52,741
[Jalil] <i>This is their schedule</i>
<i>in 36 minutes.</i>

428
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:55,619
[Jalil, in English] <i>Agent Angeles,</i>
<i>we are in position.</i>

429
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:58,705
[in English] They won't even know
what's coming.
